# Demo 4 — The Mirror — Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Ship the "Mirror" misconception demo on the landing page — a chat-style surface with a single togglable phrase in the user prompt that flips the agent's confidently-worded answer to its opposite. The parts of the response that change wear a brief amber flash on toggle. After the user has seen both framings, a single italic line fades in below the chat. A small "rubber duck" expandable sits beneath the demo.

**Architecture:** New demo lives in `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/mirror/`, parallel to the existing `completion/` and `plausibility/` directories. Two pre-written agent responses (ship-first / tests-first) are encoded as parallel arrays of `{ kind: "shared" | "differ"; content: ReactNode }` segments so the renderer can apply a flash highlight to differing spans only. Toggle state (current framing, seen-set, monotonic flashKey) lives in the top-level `<Mirror>` client component. The flash is implemented via a CSS animation registered in `apps/web/app/styles.css`; differing spans are remounted on toggle (via React `key`) so the animation re-runs on mount. Wrapper-level copy is passed through the existing `MisconceptionWrapper`. The current "Sketch" placeholder for misconception #4 in `page.tsx` is replaced with `<Mirror />`, and the `tag` prop changes from `"Sketch"` to `"Mirror"`.

**Tech Stack:** Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Tailwind 4.1, Biome 2.3 (ultracite presets), Bun 1.1. No new npm dependencies.

**Verification approach:** `apps/web` has no test framework. Each task ends with `cd apps/web && bun run typecheck` (`tsc --noEmit`), `bun run check` from the repo root (Biome), and a commit. The final task includes `bun run check`, `cd apps/web && bun run typecheck`, `turbo build --filter=web`, and full manual browser verification against the definition-of-done items in the spec. Do **not** introduce a test framework into `apps/web` as part of this plan.

