  "tests-first": TESTS_FIRST_SEGMENTS,
};

// Module-load invariant: both framings must produce the same sequence of
// segment kinds, so the renderer can pair them index-by-index. If you edit
// the segments and break this, the assertion fires loudly in dev.
{
  const shipKinds = SHIP_FIRST_SEGMENTS.map((s) => s.kind).join(",");
  const testKinds = TESTS_FIRST_SEGMENTS.map((s) => s.kind).join(",");
  if (shipKinds !== testKinds) {
    throw new Error(
      `Mirror demo: response segment shape mismatch. ship-first=[${shipKinds}] tests-first=[${testKinds}]`
    );
  }
}
```

A note on the segment shape: the two responses share identical structure — an opening shared phrase, a differing position, a shared connector, a differing reason block, a shared `<em>after</em>` token, an empty differ slot (used to keep alignment when one side has no extra prose at that index), a shared introduction to the code, a differing code block, and a differing closing sentence.

The third `differ` slot in `TESTS_FIRST_SEGMENTS` is an intentionally empty string. The corresponding slot in `SHIP_FIRST_SEGMENTS` carries content. They must both exist (the invariant requires equal length and matching kinds at each index); they are not required to have identical lengths of *visible text*. A `differ` segment with `content: ""` simply renders nothing visible — the flash on toggle is invisible there, which is fine.

